['\n<p align="center">\n\t<span style="font-size:12px;"><strong>Race Area</strong></span></p>\n<p align="center">\n\t<strong><img alt="" src="data:image/png;base64," /></strong></p>\n<p align="center">\n\t&nbsp;</p>\n<p>\n\t<strong>Distance to race area</strong></p>\n<ul>\n\t<li>\n\t\tCourses will be laid on open water north and west of Howth harbour between the islands of Lambay and Ireland&rsquo;s Eye</li>\n\t<li>\n\t\tTime to racecourse &ndash; on average, between 15 and 30 minutes</li>\n\t<li>\n\t\tObstructions between harbour mouth and Race Area are clearly marked with buoys</li>\n</ul>\n<p>\n\t<img alt="" src="data:image/png;base64," /></p>\n<p>\n\t&nbsp;</p>\n<p>\n\t<strong>Course Rotation</strong></p>\n<ul>\n\t<li>\n\t\tRacing waters are on a 12 km stretch between Lambay Island and Ireland&rsquo;s Eye island. Courses can be rotated through all points of the compass with minimal influence from surrounding land masses.</li>\n\t<li>\n\t\tApprox. 15m deep race area</li>\n\t<li>\n\t\tNo Commercial Traffic</li>\n</ul>\n<p>\n\t&nbsp;</p>\n<p>\n\t<strong>Tidal/topographical influence</strong></p>\n<p>\n\t&nbsp;</p>\n<ul>\n\t<li>\n\t\tTides in race area flow generally in a north-south direction and are non-spring tides for the proposed and alternative dates for the event.</li>\n\t<li>\n\t\tThe race area is outside those locations which are subject to complex tidal flows, such as the immediate environs of Ireland&rsquo;s Eye.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>\n\t<img alt="" src="data:image/png;base64," /></p>\n<p>\n\t&nbsp;</p>\n<ul>\n\t<li>\n\t\tLandmasses &ndash; the race area has a low-lying landmass to the west and has minimal effect on wind direction or flow.
